OL,3,CWhat happens now as former Labour MP
OL,4,CMike Amesbury jailed?
OL,6,FPeter Stanyon, Chief Executive of the
OL,7,FAssociation of Electoral
OL,8,FAdministrators (AEA), said: "An MP
OL,9,Fbeing convicted of an offence and
OL,10,Freceiving a custodial sentence
OL,11,F(including suspended) automatically
OL,12,Ftriggers a recall petition.
OL,14,F"A petition is open for six weeks, and
OL,15,Fif at least 10% of voters in the
OL,16,Fconstituency sign it, the MP loses
OL,17,Ftheir seat and a by-election is
OL,18,Ftriggered.
